        <ArticleTitle>Probiotic supplementation in Crohn's disease: a randomised controlled trial.</ArticleTitle>
        <Abstract>
          <AbstractText>Background: Gut microbiome dysbiosis is implicated in Crohn's disease.</AbstractText>
          <AbstractText Label="METHODS">Adults with active Crohn's disease received probiotic supplementation or placebo for 12 weeks.</AbstractText>
          <AbstractText Label="RESULTS">Probiotic supplementation significantly improved disease activity scores compared to placebo (p&lt;0.001).</AbstractText>
          <AbstractText Label="CONCLUSIONS">Probiotic supplementation may benefit patients with Crohn's disease.</AbstractText>
        </Abstract>
